            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738987916-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738987916-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the top and bottom off your <strong>pomegranate[s]</strong>, then slice into quarters</p><p>Add the <strong>pomegranate quarters</strong> to a large bowl filled with <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Tip: This helps prevent mess and makes separating the pith easier!</p><p>Separate the <strong>pomegranate seeds </strong>from the <strong>white pith </strong>and discard the pith, then drain the <strong>pomegranate seeds</strong> in a fine sieve and return to the large bowl</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688738993093-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688738993093-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688738993093-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688738993093-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688738993093-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the top and bottom off your <strong>orange[s]</strong>, then cut the <strong>skin</strong> away from the <strong>flesh</strong> and discard the skin</p><p>Slice the <strong>orange flesh </strong>into rounds</p><p>Strip your <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>thyme leaves</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>thyme honey</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
